         <abstract>
           <p>The attribution of the hymn to John the Evangelist is based on <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/7WA33SUX"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Chaine1913Rep"/><title level="a">Répertoire des Salam et Malkeʾe contenus dans les manuscrits éthiopiens des bibliothèques d’Europe</title><title level="j">Revue de l’Orient Chrétien</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Marius</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Chaîne</t:surname></author><date>1913</date><biblScope unit="volume">18</biblScope><biblScope unit="issue">2 and 4 (Deuxième série, 8/2 and 8/4)</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">183–203 and 337–357</biblScope><note type="url">http://catholicapedia.net/Documents/Revue-de-l.Orient-chretien/18-1913_revue-de-l.orient-ch_paris.pdf</note></bibl>. However,
           according to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/MIFKZCUN"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Wright1877BM"/><title level="m">Catalogue of the Ethiopic Manuscripts in the British Museum Acquired since the Year 1847</title><author><forename>William</forename><surname>Wright</surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Gilbert and Rivington</publisher><date>1877</date><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/catalogueofethio00brituoft</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Wright1877BM</note><note type="tag">British Museum</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Wright1877BM</note><note type="tag">British Museum</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note></bibl> it is addressed to John the Baptist, whereas
         <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/IHMFEASA"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:EMML7"/><title level="m">A Catalogue of Ethiopian Manuscripts Microfilmed for the Ethiopian Manuscript Microfilm Library, Addis Ababa, and for the Hill Monastic Manuscript Library, Collegeville, VII: Project Numbers 2501–3000</title><author><name>Getatchew Haile</name></author><author><forename>William F.</forename><surname>Macomber</surname></author><pubPlace>Collegeville, MN</pubPlace><publisher>Hill Monastic Manuscript Library, St. John's Abbey and University</publisher><date>1983</date><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/EMMLCatalog07</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">EMML</note><note type="tag">bm:EMML7</note></note><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">EMML</note><note type="tag">bm:EMML7</note><citedRange unit="page">104-105</citedRange></bibl> ascribes it to emperor <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10375Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs I</persName>.</p>
         </abstract>
